==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|local|ize}}. Compare French {{term|localiser|lang=fr}}.

===Alternative forms===
* (UK) [[localise]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|localiz|ing}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To make [[local]]; to fix in, or [[assign]] to, a definite place.
#* {{quote-book|title=Memorials of a Tour in Italy|year=1837|section=Musings near Aquapendente|author=William Wordsworth|url=http://www.bartleby.com/145/ww881.html|passage=Out of her early struggles well inspired / To '''localize''' heroic acts}}
# {{context|software|_|engineering|lang=en}} To adapt a product for use in a particular country or region, typically by translating text into the language of that country or region and, if necessary, ensuring support of different character sets.
#: ''We need to '''localize''' our software for the Japanese market.''

